2026-03-30 | Make Strings Equal with Even Distance Swaps

	Question
Check if we can rearrange s1 to make it equal to s2.

	Approach
1.	Split both strings into two groups:
		even indices  
		odd indices  

2.	For both strings:
		count frequency of characters in:
			even positions  
			odd positions  

3.	If both groups match:
		return true  
	Else:
		return false  

	Time Complexity
	O(n)

	Space Complexity
	O(1) (26 letters)

	Solution

class Solution {
public:
    bool canBeEqual(string s1, string s2) {

        vector<int> even1(26,0), odd1(26,0);
        vector<int> even2(26,0), odd2(26,0);

        int n = s1.size();

        for(int i=0;i<n;i++){
            if(i % 2 == 0){
                even1[s1[i]-'a']++;
                even2[s2[i]-'a']++;
            } else {
                odd1[s1[i]-'a']++;
                odd2[s2[i]-'a']++;
            }
        }

        return even1 == even2 && odd1 == odd2;
    }
};

	Key Insight
Swaps preserve **index parity groups**.  
So the problem reduces to:
		matching frequency of characters in even and odd positions separately.
